2021 Narrative:
- Training course on "Cryptocurrency Investigation" was held by the Regional Programme for Afghanistan and Neighboring countries jointly with GPML. Representatives from law enforcement bodies and the Ministry fo Economy and Finance of Turkmenistan participated in the training. The participants got a deeper insight into the customer due diligence and criticality of regulation and supervision and developed skills on cryptocurrency investigation to mitigae money laundering.
- 1 round (7-months long) of the English language training for Turkmen law enforcement officers completed in August 2021 involving 44 representatives of law enforcement and judiciary bodies;
- 2 round (7-months long) of the English language training for Turkmen law enforcement officers launched in November 2021 involving 65 representatives of law enforcement and judiciary bodies;
- Online consultations on international judiciary cooperation and Mutual legal assistance in investigation of trafficking in persons cases conducted in June 2021 with participation of counter-TIP authorities of the Republic of Turkey;

